        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down. | Bromley. | Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Feb 7<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>.</date>
                    <salute>My dear M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Forbes</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am much obliged for your note, and am sorry that I troubled you with the pamplet, as you already possessed it. I dare say the man is mad. He wrote to me boasting that he should revolutionize geology.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>With respect to my own book, the subject grows so, that I really cannot say when I shall go to press; but I know that in about two months, I shall have to go again over that part of my MS., where I should like to insert a short abstract of your most interesting observations on the Aymara Indiens, and I should be most grateful if you could let me have it by that time.<ref target="#foot.f3"/> I am glad to hear that you are thinking of publishing a paper on the Indians in extenso.<ref target="#foot.f4"/></p>
<p>I hope that you will be soon well,<ref target="#foot.f5"/> and pray believe me | yours very sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p>
<p>P.S. Owing to your letter being addressed to Q. Anne St, I did not receive until yesterday.<ref target="#foot.f6"/></p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.2 me] <hi rend="italic">interl in CD’s hand</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n2">2.2 again] <hi rend="italic">interl in CD’s hand</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n3">2.6 on the Indians] <hi rend="italic">interl in CD’s hand</hi> </note>
