        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6584.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from David Forbes, 30 January 1869</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6584.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from David Forbes, 30 January 1869</ref>. CD refers to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2562.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Gustav Jenzsch</ref> and <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_4185.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Jenzsch 1868</ref>. Jenzsch’s letter to CD has not been found.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref> was published in 1871, by which time CD was able to refer to Forbes’s published work on the Aymara people (D. Forbes 1870).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6584.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from David Forbes, 30 January 1869</ref> and n. 5.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">In his letter of 30 January 1869, Forbes mentioned suffering a bad attack of bronchitis.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f6">Forbes evidently sent his letter to the address of CD’s brother, <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1211.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Erasmus Alvey Darwin</ref>. In 1869, CD stayed with his brother from 16 to 24 February (see ‘Journal’ (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 17, Appendix II)).</note>
        </div>        
            
